        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 6:58AM CST by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 658 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
New London, or 7 miles southwest of Kilgore, moving northeast at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Longview, Kilgore, White Oak, Hallsville, Overton, New London,
Clarksville City, Liberty City, Lakeport, Rolling Meadows, Judson
and Laird Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
